    {
      "id": "declaration-contract-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Overview",
      "position": {
        "x": 740,
        "y": -180
      },
      "width": 660,
      "height": 380,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Core Rule\n\nA `.node` graph should begin with one **declaration** node.\n\nThe declaration is the first authoritative thing a reader interprets.\n\nIt should state:\n- graph identity\n- authority and mutation policy\n- dependencies and settings\n- what artifact the graph is\n- what primary surface the graph exposes\n- which node actually owns that surface\n\n## Required practical consequence\n\nA declaration should not stop at identity prose.\n\nFor a normal graph, the declaration should also say:\n- `data.declaration.kind: graph`\n- `data.declaration.targetMode: artifact`\n- `data.declaration.artifactKind: graph`\n- `data.declaration.defaultSurfaceId`: a real surface id\n- `data.declaration.surfaces`: real declared surfaces\n- `viewNodeId`: the node that actually renders a declared view surface\n\n## Intended Consequence\n\nIf declaration becomes canonical, `manifest` stops being a required separate primitive.\n\nA manifest may survive only as:\n- legacy compatibility data\n- or an older specialization that declaration replaces during migration.\n\n## Optional Analytics Boundary\n\n`data.analytics` is optional declaration-owned metadata. Its absence is a complete and deliberate untracked state. The presence of a valid object, including `{}`, opts the graph into runtime-managed virtual page views.\n\nAuthored fields are limited to optional `pageTitle` and `contentGroup`. The graph must not supply `page_location`, measurement configuration, arbitrary event parameters, dispatch instructions, or viewer consent state. Twilite derives the HTTPS launch URL and owns dispatch, deduplication, and viewer-level policy.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "markdown",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "declaration-contract-shape",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Minimum Shape",
      "position": {
        "x": 740,
        "y": 250
      },
      "width": 400,
      "height": 460,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Minimum Shape\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"declaration\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"identity\": {},\n    \"intent\": {},\n    \"authority\": {},\n    \"dependencies\": {},\n    \"settings\": {},\n    \"document\": {},\n    \"declaresKind\": \"graph\",\n    \"declaration\": {\n      \"kind\": \"graph\",\n      \"targetMode\": \"artifact\",\n      \"artifactKind\": \"graph\",\n      \"defaultSurfaceId\": \"reader\",\n      \"surfaces\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"reader\",\n          \"kind\": \"view\",\n          \"label\": \"Reader\",\n          \"memo\": \"Primary reading surface.\",\n          \"viewNodeId\": \"reader-node-id\"\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Reading Rule\n\nReaders should interpret the graph through the declaration first, then read the remaining nodes in that light.\n\nThat gives one obvious starting point instead of splitting graph identity from graph declaration.\n\n### Optional analytics extension\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"declaration\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"analytics\": {\n      \"pageTitle\": \"Optional reporting title\",\n      \"contentGroup\": \"people\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis object is intentionally outside `data.declaration`: it describes whether and how the declared graph participates in runtime analytics, not what artifact or surface the declaration exposes. Do not add it by default.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "markdown",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "declaration-contract-migration",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Migration Rule",
      "position": {
        "x": 1180,
        "y": 250
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 460,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Migration Rule\n\nDeclaration is a forward contract.\n\nMigration should proceed like this:\n1. draft the declaration primitive\n2. let new templates target declaration first\n3. keep reading `manifest` for compatibility during transition\n4. collapse manifest-first assumptions only after template and runtime paths are stable\n\nThis avoids broad destructive migration while still moving the system toward a cleaner starting point.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "markdown",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown"
      }
    },
